<br>
I know the mana drain componant adds a extra resist check, but that's really only if the mob actually has mana. Not to mention when it's not resisted, it's doing damage AND draining mana (though not very much really). It's a magic based spell, one of the easiest resists to lower (occlusion of sound, tash, malosini all stack and lower magic resist), so unless your solo, getting resist rates improved isn't so bad. Which is why I personally think Maelstorm of Electricty sucks, it's an inferior spell that costs more mana and requires a higher level. It's also a PITA to get, it should be alot better. Or manastorm should have had it's mana drain componant removed and Maelstorm would never needed to be made.<br>
